Difficult events in a woman’s life (for example, loss of a job, death of a loved one) can influence her #mental health. If these occurred during the year before (or during) her pregnancy, they can put her at risk for experiencing #mental illness. #MentalHealthMatters @UnitedGMH

Previous pregnancy loss (for example, a miscarriage, stillbirth or abortion) or the loss of an infant or child, put women at greater risk of suffering from a #mental illness during pregnancy. #MentalHealthMatters  @UnitedGMH  @SJonesCigsKills  @KevinKNaruse  @johnallenacamp

Women who live in poverty have the added stresses of unemployment, poor housing and food insecurity. If they develop a #mental illness, they are more likely to experience isolation and stigma, have limited ability to generate income. #mentalhealth  @johnallenacamp  @ForAffair

Children of mothers with #mental illness are more likely to: Have social problems. Perform poorly at school. Develop #mental illness themselves.#Mental illness in the mother can negatively affect the infant and child. #mentalhealth  @SJonesCigsKills  @KevinKNaruse  @ForAffair

Difficult events in a woman’s life (for example, loss of a job, death of a loved one) can influence her #mental health. If these occurred during the year before (or during) her pregnancy, they can put her at risk for experiencing #mental illness. #MentalHealthMatters @UnitedGMH

Previous pregnancy loss (for example, a miscarriage, stillbirth or abortion) or the loss of an infant or child, put women at greater risk of suffering from a #mental illness during pregnancy. #MentalHealthMatters  @UnitedGMH  @SJonesCigsKills  @KevinKNaruse  @johnallenacamp

Women who live in poverty have the added stresses of unemployment, poor housing and food insecurity. If they develop a #mental illness, they are more likely to experience isolation and stigma, have limited ability to generate income. #mentalhealth  @johnallenacamp  @ForAffair

Children of mothers with #mental illness are more likely to: Have social problems. Perform poorly at school. Develop #mental illness themselves.#Mental illness in the mother can negatively affect the infant and child. #mentalhealth  @SJonesCigsKills  @KevinKNaruse  @ForAffair

THE EFFECT OF #MENTAL ILLNESS DURING PREGNANCY ON INFANT AND CHILD. #Mental illness in pregnant women is associated with: Poor fetal growth. Preterm delivery and low birth weight. Infants that are more vulnerable to infection and disease. #mentalhealth @UnitedGMH  @rhdphd

On the other hand, #mental illness is a psychological or emotional condition which prevents a person from functioning normally, over a period of time. It can disrupt a person’s thoughts, emotions or behaviour. #MentalHealthAwareness  @UnitedGMH  @Cemhri  @AfricaAmhec  @ForAffair

Difficult events in a woman’s life (for example, loss of a job, death of a loved one) can influence her #mental health. If these occurred during the year before (or during) her pregnancy, they can put her at risk for experiencing #mental illness. #MentalHealthMatters @UnitedGMH

Previous pregnancy loss (for example, a miscarriage, stillbirth or abortion) or the loss of an infant or child, put women at greater risk of suffering from a #mental illness during pregnancy. #MentalHealthMatters  @UnitedGMH  @SJonesCigsKills  @KevinKNaruse  @johnallenacamp

Women who live in poverty have the added stresses of unemployment, poor housing and food insecurity. If they develop a #mental illness, they are more likely to experience isolation and stigma, have limited ability to generate income. #mentalhealth  @johnallenacamp  @ForAffair

Children of mothers with #mental illness are more likely to: Have social problems. Perform poorly at school. Develop #mental illness themselves.#Mental illness in the mother can negatively affect the infant and child. #mentalhealth  @SJonesCigsKills  @KevinKNaruse  @ForAffair

THE EFFECT OF #MENTAL ILLNESS DURING PREGNANCY ON INFANT AND CHILD. #Mental illness in pregnant women is associated with: Poor fetal growth. Preterm delivery and low birth weight. Infants that are more vulnerable to infection and disease. #mentalhealth @UnitedGMH  @rhdphd

On the other hand, #mental illness is a psychological or emotional condition which prevents a person from functioning normally, over a period of time. It can disrupt a person’s thoughts, emotions or behaviour. #MentalHealthAwareness  @UnitedGMH  @Cemhri  @AfricaAmhec  @ForAffair
